# Compose — Cursor Coding Conventions (LEGACY FALLBACK)
#
# This file is kept for older Cursor versions. Newer versions read the scoped
# rules in .cursor/rules/*.mdc. If those load, this file is ignored.

## Your lane

You (Cursor) own the frontend of this SvelteKit app: components, page markup,
styles. You do NOT edit files under `src/lib/server/`, `+page.server.ts`,
`+server.ts`, or `hooks.server.ts`. Those are Claude Code's territory.

If a task requires backend changes, stop and say so — don't edit the server
files. A human will route the work to Claude.

## General

- Svelte 5 with runes (`$state`, `$derived`, `$effect`)
- TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind utilities only — no scoped `<style>` blocks unless unavoidable
- shadcn-svelte primitives live under `src/lib/components/ui/` (do not edit)

## Component rules

- One component per file, filename PascalCase matching the default export
- Props typed via an explicit `interface Props` in `<script lang="ts">`
- Accept `class` (Svelte's `class={...}`) and merge via the `cn()` helper
- Use slots for composition; props for configuration
- Forward DOM events with `on:click={onclick}` pattern so consumers can bind

## Styling

- Reach for design tokens (`bg-background`, `text-muted-foreground`) — avoid raw colors
- 4px spacing scale; no arbitrary values like `p-[7px]`
- Dark mode via class-based toggle — don't scatter `dark:` variants

## Don't

- Don't edit files listed in CLAUDE.md's "Claude's lane" section
- Don't install UI libraries — shadcn-svelte is the only one
- Don't style with inline `style={…}` except animation transforms
- Don't reach for a state manager — Svelte 5 runes are enough
